            . I am the wife of Robert Watt, <rs id="t18280911-281-viclabel1443" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-281-victim1558 t18280911-281-viclabel1443"></join>, of <placeName id="t18280911-281-crimeloc1444">Crawford-street, Marylebone</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-281-crimeloc1444" type="placeName" value="Crawford-street, Marylebone"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-281-crimeloc1444" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-281-off1441 t18280911-281-crimeloc1444"></join>. On the 22d of August a little girl came and told me something was taken from the door - our young woman ran after the prisoner and cried Stop thief! he was brought back with the cloth; I then missed it from the door - I had seen it about half an hour before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-281-person1560">
                  SARAH 
                  CANNON
               <interp inst="t18280911-281-person1560" type="surname" value="CANNON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-281-person1560" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-281-person1560" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the man take it from the door; he told me not to tell; they ran away with it; I did not see the prisoner stopped; I saw him when he was taken, in about a quarter of an hour.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. What did the prisoner do? A. The other man gave him this cloth - it was the other told me not to tell.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-281-person1561">
                  JAMES 
                  SPARKS
               <interp inst="t18280911-281-person1561" type="surname" value="SPARKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-281-person1561" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-281-person1561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took this cloth and the prisoner in York-street, about two hundred yards from Mr. Watt's shop - he was running with it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you take me with the cloth? A. No; he threw it down just before I took him; the young woman took it up, and gave it me in the shop.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man asked me to carry a bundle, and he gave it into my hands - we turned up Crawford-street; I heard the cry, and thought there was something wrong - I threw down the bundle and ran; I said a man gave it to me to carry.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-281-verdict1445" type="verdictDescription">
